					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the third pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year [21]: 927-28 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the reign of Madiraikoṇḍa Parakēsari. The date which is not clear on the impression in the office had been subsequently read <hi rend="italic">in situ.</hi> </p>						

						<p>It records an endowment of 90 sheep for a perpetual lamp for god Āḷvar in Tirumaṟaikkāḍu, a <hi rend="italic">perundēvadāṉa</hi> in Umbaḷa-nāḍu, by a native of Ārvala-kkūṟṟam. The measure <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
